summary: In this context, 1,1,2-trichloroethene and dichlorobis(ethylenediamine)rhodium(III) are both mentioned in relation to the study of reductive dechlorination processes. However, there is no direct interaction or specific relationship discussed between the two compounds. The focus is on the abiotic reactions involving various electron donors and the transformation of chlorinated aliphatic hydrocarbons (CAHs) rather than on the specific roles of these two chemicals.
